{
  "texts": [
    "For the stellar source category with higher activity levels, the top envelope of the log R EXT Hα versus log R median Hα distribution is largely along a positive correlation line and shows a gradual increase with log R median Hα; while for the stellar source category with lower activity levels, the top envelope of the distribution first increases and then decreases with log R median Hα, and finally intersects the top envelope of the stellar source category with higher activity levels at about log R median Hα = -4.85.",
    "The result in Section 5.3 also shows the different properties of the log R EXT Hα distribution in the T eff -log R median Hα parameter space for the stellar source categories with lower and higher activity levels.",
    "Because of their distinct behaviors of Hα variability, in our analysis the two categories of stellar sources are separated where appropriate, as performed in the previous sections.",
    "Two types of Hα variability: long-term cyclic and random.",
    "The analysis of the log R EXT Hα distribution with T span in Section 5.2 shows that, for the stellar source category with lower activity levels (log R median Hα < -4.85), the large log R EXT Hα values near the top envelope of the log R EXT Hα versus log R median Hα distribution tend to be associated with the long-term variations of Hα activity."
  ]
}